  "school": "ICT",
  "asset": "GBPUSD",
  "timeframe": "1D / 15M",
  "market_context": "GBP/USD on the daily filled a prior daily fair value gap then displaced aggressively higher, making a new high. The displacement range is marked from high to low, with a smaller fair value gap left above as a draw on liquidity. Price then swept Monday/Friday highs and closed back in.",
  "key_observation": "After aggressive displacement, price drawing back into discount of the range offers a long opportunity, with the daily fair value gap above acting as the upside target. Entering at OTE rather than equilibrium dramatically improves risk-to-reward (3.43R vs 1.6R).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the daily fair value gap that price filled, followed by a new high and aggressive displacement range.",
    "Mark the displacement range from high to low to define premium and discount zones; locate a smaller fair value gap in discount as a PD array to draw price back.",
    "Note the next-day sweep of Monday and Friday's high and a close back in, signalling a drop to fill the discount fair value gap.",
    "On the following day, observe a raid of previous day low with a close back in, with the daily fair value gap remaining above as the draw on liquidity.",
    "Drop to the 15-minute chart, mark midnight open and Asia range high/low, and watch price sweep the Asia low and fill the lower fair value gap.",
    "After the aggressive move higher on 15-minute, mark a new discount/premium range and apply Fibonacci OTE levels (0.62–0.79).",
    "Enter long at the OTE zone with target set at the daily fair value gap, yielding 3.43R versus only 1.6R at equilibrium.",
    "Confirm validity by observing no candle closes below the OTE level — price respects the entry zone before expanding higher into the daily fair value gap."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade played out: price respected the OTE entry zone with no closes below, reached the daily fair value gap target and continued higher beyond it, delivering at least 3.43R.",
  "lessons": "Framing trades using premium/discount of an aggressive displacement range and entering at OTE rather than equilibrium provides significantly better risk-to-reward. Always identify a PD array in discount for the draw and a fair value gap above as the target before executing.",
